    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "thanks for those. they're a good start but a bit surface-level for a high school policy round. my students need to move past the basics. can you expand on the legal/philosophical side of the 'rule of law' argument? like, why is the distinction between legal and illegal entry considered a fundamental moral or civic necessity rather than just a bureaucratic detail? make it really compelling for them.",
