      "content": "The principle of the rule of law demands that immigration be governed by established, transparent legal processes, not by uncontrolled entry. Allowing mass illegal entry fundamentally erodes the concept of a sovereign nation-state, as it implies that the laws of the host country are optional for those who choose to bypass them. This isn't just bureaucracy; it is a moral imperative to uphold the social contract, ensuring that all residents, legal or otherwise, operate within a predictable and lawful framework.",
